steps for set up from a git hub location with out anything stood up on the home pc 

1. create a dir on local pc (ex. /home/workspace/projectName
2. clone git repo from github in the directory you want it 
	- cmd: git clone https://github.com/username/git repo -> git clone https://github.com/wigtoy-llc/hiStepperShow.git
3. open folder in vs code 
4. run cmd: npm install
5. check install by running cmd: ng serve 
6. open a browser and go to localhost:4200

INSTALLING BOOTSTRAP 

1. run cmd: npm install --save bootstrap 
2. run cmd: npm install --save jquery
3. open angular.json and add the following to the following locations 

	projects->architect->build->styles array
		- ./node_modules/bootstrap/dist/css/bootstrap.css
	projects->architect->build->scripts array
	 	- ./node_modules/bootstrap/dist/js/bootstrap.js
		- ./node_modules/jquery/dist/jquery.js
		
4. ng serve and check to see if you have bootstrap styling using the debuger and checking imports





